==[[龙马奇团]]==
*The title is a reference to the tabletop role-playing game [[wikipedia:Dungeons & Dragons|Dungeons &amp; Dragons]], which has had two in-universe counterparts—Ogres & Oubliettes and Dragons & Dragons—introduced in the [[IDW comics]].
*The tiny Discord's running sounds is the sound used for [[wikipedia:Fred Flintstone|Fred Flintstone]] revving up his Flintmobile.
*"Discord as basketball player" "was inspired by actual real sports."<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TheBiggestJim/status/770616608087605249|title=The Biggest Jerk on Twitter: "@FrankieFoster2 @AndreaLibman No. That was inspired by actual real sports."|author=Jim Miller|publisher=Twitter|date=2016-08-30|accessdate=2016-09-02}}</ref>
*Discord's entrance music is similar to the song "[[wikipedia:Get Ready for This|Get Ready for This]]" by [[wikipedia:2 Unlimited|2 Unlimited]].
*Discord's dance club and zoot suit are a reference to the 1994 film ''[[Wikipedia:The Mask (film)|The Mask]]''.
*A background Earth pony mare dancing in the club scene bears a resemblance to [[Wikipedia:Betty Boop|Betty Boop]].
**Another background Earth pony mare bears a resemblance to African-American dancer [[wikipedia:Josephine Baker|Josephine Baker]] aka "Chiquita Banana".
*In one scene, Discord, Spike, and Big McIntosh recreate [[Wikipedia:Cassius Marcellus Coolidge|Cassius Marcellus Coolidge]]'s 1904 painting "A Friend in Need", part of the ''[[Wikipedia:Dogs Playing Poker|Dogs Playing Poker]]'' series of paintings.
*Spike and Discord's role-playing characters Garbunkle and Captain Wuzz bear resemblances to [[Wikipedia:Gandalf|Gandalf]] and [[Wikipedia:Legolas|Legolas]] respectively of the ''[[Wikipedia:The Lord of the Rings|Lord of the Rings]]'' and ''[[Wikipedia:The Hobbit|Hobbit]]'' book/film series.
*Big McIntosh's character Sir McBiggun wears a helmet resembling the Dragon born helmet from ''[[Wikipedia:The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim|The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim]]''.
*The symbol on the Squizard's amulet is the "Super S" or "Stussy", a stylized "S" commonly drawn by elementary school students.

